The Inspector General of Police IGP Mohammed Adamu has said due to the recent incidents of armed banditry, kidnapping and armed robbery especially in the Northern States, there is need for the speedy roll-out of the Community Policing strategy across the country.  IGP Adamu who said this today in Abuja stated that the plan will involve setting up of Community Policing Committees CPCs at Ward, Local Government and States levels including the Federal Capital Territory.  Our correspondent Nathan Williams reports that the Police boss also noted that the success of the community policing initiative in Nigeria depends largely on the extent that strategic Police managers understand its concept and practice.  The police boss however reiterated that the Nigerian police will continue to initiate strategies and undertake coordinated operations directed at taking the battle to the door steps of criminal elements. 